# MCP Framework Coding Standards

## Class Structure

1. Base Classes
   - Must be abstract classes
   - Must be in the appropriate namespace (`MCP\Models`, `MCP\Controllers`, `MCP\Presenters`)
   - Must follow PSR-4 autoloading standards

2. Properties
   - Protected visibility for framework properties
   - Clear and descriptive property names
   - Type hints where possible

3. Methods
   - Public methods for external API
   - Protected methods for internal framework use
   - Private methods for class-specific utilities

## Error Handling

1. Exception Management
   - Use try-catch blocks for database operations
   - Log errors using the provided logger
   - Throw exceptions up the stack when appropriate

2. Validation
   - Input validation in controllers
   - Data validation in models
   - Response validation in presenters

## Testing

1. Test Structure
   - One test class per framework class
   - Test methods named descriptively
   - Setup and teardown methods where needed

2. Coverage Requirements
   - 100% coverage for base classes
   - All public methods must be tested
   - Edge cases must be covered

## Documentation

1. Code Comments
   - DocBlocks for classes and methods
   - Inline comments for complex logic
   - Clear parameter and return type documentation

2. Example Usage
   - Provide example implementations
   - Document common use cases
   - Include error handling examples
